snippet.textDisplay: This is nothing short of an almost magical composition and rendition by everyone in this video. To have the song starting and ending with the xylophone, which alone conveys to anyone familiar with Hindi film music the memory of infancy or childhood, to the shehnai at 4:13 introducing the coming of age, the emotion of pain at 5:46, and the synthesis of loving self-reference from both the infant and adult girl child, all woven in to create a rich and moving experience for the listener. I first heard this song (many times over) a few months ago, and ever since my daughter was born, I find that I cannot separate the two.experiences, that of enjoying holding and watching her grow and thinking how precious the bond between a father and his daughter is to both. Immense thanks go to Sachin-Jigar and the band, singers for creating something truly unforgettable for as long as I believe I might live.
